<subSubSection lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,151,258]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,151,177]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Body oblong-oval, slightly convex above, shining, closely covered with short brownish setae throughout. Coloration of head, labrum, antennomeres I–III, pronotum, scutellum, meso- and metaventrites yellowish-orange; mouthparts, antennomeres IV–VII, legs and elytra dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="66" pageNumber="67" startId="66.[151,255,1955,1979]" targetBox="[183,1391,304,1929]" targetPageId="66">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,1955,2013]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1955,1979]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">FIGURE 43.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1918" box="[304,599,1956,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrous">
<emphasis box="[304,476,1956,1979]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Scirtes dichrous</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, male. A) tergite VIII, B) tergite IX, C) sternite IX, D) tegmen and penis in ventral aspect.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,152,978]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Head moderate in size, almost flat on dorsal surface, finely punctate; clypeus rather long, slightly expanded antero-laterally, almost straight in front margin. Eyes moderate in size, slightly prominent; the distance between the eyes ca. 2.3 times as long as the maximum diameter of an eye. Antennae slender, antennomeres VIII–XI lacking in the 
<typeStatus box="[517,623,272,298]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">holotype</typeStatus>
. Pronotum slightly convex above, punctured as on head; front and lateral margins almost straight; antero-lateral angles ca. 90º, gently projecting anteriorly; postero-lateral angles right-angled; posterior margin gently bisinuate; PW/PL 3.00. Scutellum moderate in size, finely punctate, equilateral-triangular. Elytra oblong, slightly convex above, widest at the middle, closely and strongly punctate; humeral portions slightly elevated; EL/EW 1.27; EL/PL 5.44; EW/PW 1.42; TL/EW 1.51. Hind tibial spurs gently curved laterally; dorsal spurs ca. 2.0 times as long as ventral ones, hind tarsi 1 absent in the 
<typeStatus box="[151,258,512,538]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">holotype</typeStatus>
. Caudal margin of sternite VII shallowly concave. Tergite VIII moderately sclerotized, trapezoidal, bearing a row of long spines on apical margin, with a pair of long apodemes; tergite IX lightly sclerotized, apical margin membranous, bearing short spines in apical part, with a pair of stout apodemes diverging posteriorly; sternite IX almost membranous, consisting of two rectangular hemisternites, bearing distinct setae in apical part. Tegmen large, well sclerotized; basal part oblong, subpalallel-sided; parameres long, outcurved, slightly shorter than apical portion of penis, pointed at apices, covered with minute foveae. Penis elongated, well sclerotized; apical portion longer than tegmen, widened, membranous with minute serrae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,152,978]" box="[198,422,792,818]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
